  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/953",
  "title": "Callback for returned hits",
  "body": "Hello! Loving Algolia for search so far! Is there a way to access the hits from the search query? On our [search page](https://theartistunion.com/search), we want users to be able to play through searched music and then autoplay to the next song when the first one finishes. As a result, we need to be able to store the hits returned from the search query.\n\nI'm thinking the API would look something like this\n\n``` js\nsearch.addWidget(\n  instantsearch.widgets.searchBox({\n    container: '#search-box',\n    placeholder: 'Search by title or artist',\n    autofocus: true,\n    onHit: (query, hits) => {\n      this.setState({ hits: hits });\n    }\n  })\n);\n```\n\nDoes this exist? If not, how would I implement this? Thanks!\n",
